JOHANNESBURG - Newly-appointed Bafana Bafana head coach Stuart Baxter outlined unity as a main factor in improving the state of South African football, during his first official address at SAFA House on Monday afternoon.READ: Baxter named new Bafana coachBaxter outlined his plans for the national team ahead of the Africa Cup of Nations qualifier against Nigeria in June, a fixture that according to the Brit, he remains undefeated.The point of team selection was also discussed as well as Baxters apporach to monitoring foreign, and more specifically European based players. eNCA